cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the security of microprocessors and proposes a new approach to mitigate microarchitecture state attacks for interactive applications. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the impact of the proposed approach on operating systems (cs.OS) and system-level design (cs.SY), as well as the implementation of strong isolation guarantees (cs.SE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
